      "specificArticles": [
        {
          "textContent": "The trail starts from the historical center, from Casa Petri and heads to 'Tăul Mare' lake where you can freshen up a bit with the cold mountain water. From here continue towards the villages 'Muntari' and 'Poiana' through a typical landscape of 'Moților' Land, dotted with haystacks and pastures and where you can see herds of sheep or cows grazing. The walk continues until you come across a mountain ridge formed of some tall columns of basalt as in the picture above. Looks a bit scary ... isn’t it? A path will take you up on top of the ridge and the fear will disappear when you'll see the view from here. The trail is fully marked with the 'red cross' sign by Salvamont (Mountain Rescue) so it is very easy to follow. If you go cycling, please note that for the last 500 meters the climb is on a narrow path that is not accessible for bicycles.",
